# Delivery Strict Full

## Mandatory Pre-Implementation Gate
- Define objective and non-goals.
- Enumerate impacted modules/files and dependency surfaces.
- Identify API/data contract changes and compatibility impact.
- Define test plan (unit/integration/e2e) and acceptance criteria.
- Define risk and rollback strategy before editing.

## Implementation Discipline
- Use smallest safe incremental changes.
- Keep one concern per change set.
- Preserve BE/FE/DevOps boundaries and interface contracts.
- Add comments only for complex logic.

## Mandatory Validation Gate
- Run lint checks on touched files.
- Run relevant tests for changed behavior.
- Validate build/package for affected stack when feasible.
- Confirm error handling and edge cases were addressed.

## Mandatory Reporting Gate
- Report changed files by Backend/Frontend/DevOps.
- Report verification evidence (commands run and outcomes).
- Report remaining risks, assumptions, and rollback path.
- Report recommended next action before merge/release.
